   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE PRACTICAL STEPS OF GOD'S ORDAINED WAY Scripture Reading: Luke 10:1-3, 5-7; 19:5; Acts 2:46; 5:42; 1 Cor 14:26, 31, 1, 4b OUTLINE Preaching the gospel to gain people: By visiting people Luke 10:1-3, 5-7: Needing to pay a price.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Being sent as lambs into the midst of wolves.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Finding the sons of peace.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Bringing salvation to people's homes Luke 19:5, 9.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Perfecting new believers: Setting up meetings in new believers' homes.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Continuing steadfastly to meet with new believers.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Leading new believers to function in meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Establishing group meetings: Gradually bringing the new believers to form a group meeting.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Leading new believers to fellowship and care for one another mutually.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Leading them further to speak for the Lord in the meeting.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Arriving at the practice of the district meetings: Gradually bringing the cared-for ones into district meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Helping the cared-for ones to get further into the church life.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Leading the cared-for ones to speak for the Lord and to speak forth the Lord in district meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Through the saints' organic functioning, mutual speaking and supplying, and mutual establishing to build up the Body of Christ.</S>
   </TEXT>
